               Why doest thou cry vnto me (sayth God the father vnto Moyses) And yet Moyses in his prayer opened not his mouth. Therfore the spirite beyng present, doth present the prayers vnto God though all the sences els be silent. On the other side. If the hart be otherwise occupyed. God will not accept the prayers though neuer so many and neuer so laboursome. For after this maner the Lord Iesus doth recite out of Esay the Prophet. This people doth honour me with their lippes, but their hart is farre awaye from me but they worshyp me in vayne. &amp;c. Behold here worshyppyng is to no purpose, the spirite beyng absent: Why doe ye therefore spurne agaynst matters so manifest?
            
               
               
