iurisdiction, and should enterlace their owne definitiue sentences with his. These are both false. God is a ielous God, and will not geue his honour to any other. Hee hath appointed no Uicare, and the holy Scripture doth acknowledge no such word, neither was it his will, that the Apostles should entermedle in his Iurisdiction. Your surmise is false, quite contrary to his heauenly prerogatiue.
            
