                     , power.But yet truely as concernyng either the enterprising, or accomplishyng of those spirituall motions and operations, for as much as they do farre exceéde the capacitie of mans nature, the Scripture doth vtterly deny that man (beyng not as yet regenerated) is naturally endued with any force or abilitie of will sithence the first creatiō: but that all those giftes are vtterly lost through the greatnesse of Sinne, and that by this meanes 
