                  The lyke must iudged of Amasias, who had not fallen into that perill if he had harckened to Ioas the kyng of Israell, now what shall we alleadge to be the cause why he did not harken to the good counsell of Ioas? Here will Osorius runne backe againe after his wounted maner, to Freewill, or to Sathan ye mouyng cause.2. parillipo, Cap. 25. And this is true in deéde in respect of the second and instrumentall causes. But Gods sacred Oracles beyng accustomed

to searche out the souereigne and principall cause of thyngs, do rayse them selues higher, and do aunswere, that this was wrought by God him selfe, who dyd not onely suffer hym, but of his determinate counsell directed him also thereunto, bycause hee would auenge him selfe of the kyng, for his abhominable Idolatry.
                  
