                  He that draweth, draweth him that is willing. Wherfore if our owne will do carry vs headlong to Sinne, let vs not Impute it to Necessitie, but to lust.
               And therfore to make a distinction of these thynges (Osorius) and that ye may be satisfied, if it be possible. Voluntary and Necessary are not opposite. For they may both light together at one tyme in Will. When Will enlightened by the inspiration

